{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"snowwhite-mysterious-macropod","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nThe `rebar metrics` subcommand: parses `--since/--until` and optional `--bucket day|week|month`, renders the full registry over the range as JSON (default) or a text summary, and is the single entry point wiring the readers.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/_commands/metrics.py` — new: arg parsing + render loop over `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py`.\n- `src/rebar/_cli/__init__.py` — register the `metrics` read subcommand.\n- `src/rebar/_cli/help/metrics.txt` — new help text.\n- `docs/cli-reference.md` — document the command.\n- `tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py` — new CLI subprocess test.\n\n## Approach\nA thin CLI over the registry keeps the command complete-once: it iterates every `MetricSpec`, invokes its compute for the range, and emits value-or-`unavailable` per metric, so new signals appear with no CLI change. Read-only; date bucketing uses the exact HLC wall-clock timestamps; JSON is the default stdout contract, `--output text` a human summary (mirrors `rebar audit`).\n\n## Tests\n- CLI (real subprocess against a temp store): `rebar metrics --since ... --until ... --output json` exits 0 and emits a `metrics` map containing every registered id; an unpopulated metric shows `unavailable`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py` passes: `rebar metrics --since 2026-01-01 --until 2026-07-01 --output json` exits 0 and `jq -e '.metrics | keys | length > 0'` succeeds, with every registry id present.\n- [ ] `rebar metrics --help` renders the help file and the command is listed by bare `rebar` — CLI test asserts exit 0 and help contains `--since`.\n- [ ] `--bucket week` yields a per-bucket series for a metric with history — CLI test asserts the JSON contains at least one bucket key.","id":"9a5a-d9ea-47c1-4e6a","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"The rebar metrics CLI command (date-range, JSON/text, registry render)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416762857515001,"uuid":"2e4a18ea-05c2-4544-bde6-eef0194fb697"}